The paper focuses on developing fast distributed algorithms for computing sparse cuts in networks, which is a problem related to distributed computing, graph theory, and network analysis. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with large-scale graphs and networks, which are common topics in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper mentions conductance, which is a measure of the connectivity of a graph, and this is a topic in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
